en_148774_0	US President-elect Donald Trump has named Gen James Mattis, a former marine who served in Iraq and Afghanistan, as his defence secretary.
en_148774_1	"He's our best," Trump said, as he announced his pick in a speech in Ohio.
en_148774_2	Gen Mattis, who is known as "Mad Dog", was an outspoken critic of the Obama administration's Middle East policy, particularly on Iran.
en_148774_3	He has referred to Iran as "the single most enduring threat to stability and peace in the Middle East".
